1 is the intercept of the regression line of variable C with time (t) and b
1 is the slope of this regression, a
2 is the change in intercept when L is considered in the model and b
2 represents the change in the slope b
1 with changing L. JMP 10.0.0 software was used in all analyses. Statistical significance was set to p < 0.05.
